CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 22, 1940, pg. 8 reads: "The Bride Cuts The Cake - Mrs. William L. Dugas, the former Miss Henri Avant, cuts the cake, while her groom looks on. The couple was wed last Saturday evening at the bride's home in Frankstown avenue, Pittsburgh.  The groom hails from Milwaukee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group Portrait of Henri Avant Dugas, wearing gown with sheer overlay, lace trimmed veil, and large cross necklace, cutting wedding cake while William L. Dugas looks on, standing behind table with three tiered wedding cake, in home of Mr. and Mrs. J.D. Avant of 8106 Frankstown Avenue
